### Change 2 — Template detection (inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`, ~line 1644)

Insert after the Ministral-3 block, before the GPT-OSS check:

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    // Note: [SYSTEM_PROMPT] absence distinguishes this from Ministral/Magistral Large 3
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

- **Two positive markers** (`[INST]`, `[/INST]`) identify v0.3 format
- **One negative marker** (`[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent) prevents collision with the existing Ministral-3 handler
- Positioned after Ministral-3 check as an extra safety layer
